# Core (Serva)

- Use **pnpm** for scripts and installs (`pnpm dev`, `pnpm lint`, `pnpm build`).
- Keep changes **minimal and on-task**: no unrelated refactors, no extra docs unless asked.
- **Never** put real secrets or `.env` values in rules, commits, or chat; reference env var names only.
- Before inventing a new pattern, **read nearby code** in the same feature folder and match style, imports, and types.
- After substantive edits, run **`pnpm lint`** when practical.
- Repo orientation: see root **`AGENTS.md`**.

## Import conventions

- **`@serva/database`** — Prisma client, model types, DAL functions.
- **`@serva/shared`** — shared types, constants, helper utilities, auth validation schemas (e.g. `LoginSchema`, `SignupSchema`).
- **`@serva/auth`** or **`@serva/auth/<module>`** — session, authorize, permissions, cookies, password helpers.
- **`@serva/ui/components/<name>`** — shadcn primitives. **`@serva/ui/components/serva/<name>`** — Serva custom components. **`@serva/ui/lib/utils`** — `cn` utility.
- **`@/*`** — app-local paths inside each app's `src/`.

## Multi-app architecture

- **`apps/web`** (`@serva/web`) — main app (port 3000). `(admin)` route group = **tenant** admin.
- **`apps/auth`** (`@serva/auth-app`) — centralized auth portal (port 3001). Owns login, signup, password reset, company selection, invite flows.
- **`apps/admin`** (`@serva/admin-app`) — platform super-admin (port 3002). Global company/identity management for `isPlatformAdmin` users. Protected by `platformAdminGuard`.
- Consumer apps redirect to **`AUTH_URL`** for login/logout; cookies are shared via **`COOKIE_DOMAIN`** in production.
